SIMPLE: freakish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freakish
<hw>Freak"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Apt to change the mind suddenly;
whimsical; capricious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It may be a question whether the wife or the woman was the more
<qex>freakish</qex> of the two.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Freakish</qex> when well, and fretful when she's sick.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>rapidly changing and unpredictable; <as>as,
<ex>freakish</ex> weather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>markedly abnormal.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> freaky.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Freak"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Freak"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>freakishness</ent>⟦br⟧
